                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-05T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1922—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. My telegram number 66 August 5, 11 a.m. Learn … reservation … provides all
                    South American traffic shall pass through Saint Vincent in the Cape Verde
                    Islands …</p>
                <pb facs="0479" n="365" xml:id="pg_365"/>
                <p>I shall make no protest until Department has consulted Western Union and
                    instructed me. Endeavoring to secure printed text but may have to wait a few
                    days.</p>
                <p>Please instruct soonest possible. London informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
